In a press conference, President Biden addressed the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic and the importance of getting vaccinated. He emphasized the severity of the Delta variant and its high transmissibility, which has caused a new wave of cases in the United States. He urged Americans to get vaccinated, stating that vaccinated individuals are highly unlikely to get COVID-19 and that the vaccine is the best defense against the virus. He highlighted that the majority of hospitalizations and deaths are among the unvaccinated population. The President also discussed the need for global vaccination efforts and announced that the United States has shipped over 110 million doses of COVID-19 vaccines to 65 countries. He emphasized the importance of democracies working together to control the virus and lead the world in vaccination efforts. The President also called on New York Governor Andrew Cuomo to resign following the findings of a report that concluded he sexually harassed multiple women. He addressed the issue of evictions and stated that the CDC is working on a new partial eviction moratorium that may face legal challenges.